<p>The <code>ignore</code> tag escapes PAD syntax so it is not processed.</p>

<h2>Basic Ignore</h2>
<pre>{open}ignore{close}
{open}this is not processed{close}
{open}/ignore{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {ignore}{this is not processed}{/ignore}</p>

<h2>Show PAD Code</h2>
<pre>{open}ignore{close}
{open}if $condition{close}
  Show this
{open}/if{close}
{open}/ignore{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
<pre>{ignore}{if $condition}
  Show this
{/if}{/ignore}</pre>

<h2>Document Variables</h2>
<pre>{open}ignore{close}
Use {open}$name{close} to display the user's name.
Use {open}$email{close} to display their email.
{open}/ignore{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {ignore}Use {$name} to display the user's name. Use {$email} to display their email.{/ignore}</p>

<h2>Show Loop Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}ignore{close}
{open}users{close}
  &lt;li&gt;{open}$name{close}&lt;/li&gt;
{open}/users{close}
{open}/ignore{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
<pre>{ignore}{users}
  <li>{$name}</li>
{/users}{/ignore}</pre>

<h2>Mixed Content</h2>
<p>Normal variable: {set demo='Hello'}{$demo}</p>
<p>Ignored: {ignore}{$demo}{/ignore}</p>

<h2>Alternative: open/close Tags</h2>
<p>You can also use <code>{open}open{close}</code> and <code>{open}close{close}</code> to show individual braces:</p>
<pre>{open}open{close}variable{open}close{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {open}variable{close}</p>
